 across several\nproduction sites around the world. We motivate and discuss the quality control\nprocedures that were developed to standardize the performance of the detectors,\nand we present the final results of the production. Out of 161 detectors\nproduced, 156 detectors passed all tests, and 144 detectors are now installed\nin the CMS experiment. The various visual inspections, gas tightness tests,\nintrinsic noise rate characterizations, and effective gas gain and response\nuniformity tests allowed the project to achieve this high success rate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Mar 2022 20:52:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-25"}
