raints\nof $\\Omega_{m} = 0.272^{+0.032}_{-0.052}$ and $S_{8} \\equiv \\sigma_8\n\\sqrt{\\Omega_{m}/0.3}= 0.736^{+0.032}_{-0.028}$ ($\\Omega_{m} =\n0.245^{+0.026}_{-0.044}$ and $S_{8} = 0.734^{+0.035}_{-0.028}$) when assuming\nlinear (nonlinear) galaxy bias in our modeling. Considering only the\ncross-correlation of galaxy shear with CMB lensing, we find $\\Omega_{m} =\n0.270^{+0.043}_{-0.061}$ and $S_{8} = 0.740^{+0.034}_{-0.029}$. Our constraints\non $S_8$ are consistent with recent cosmic shear measurements, but lower than\nthe values preferred by primary CMB measurements from Planck.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Mar 2022 14:27:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2022 01:58:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-15"}
